      "content": "yeah i'll add more logs. but honestly it just feels so erratic. like we're following all the standard best practices for locking and state transitions, but the system still just breaks down for no apparent reason. it's like there's this invisible factor messing things up that we just can't account for in the code.\n\ndo you think there could be something deeper, like a race condition we're totally missing, or does it really just look like standard resource contention?",
